[Tuberculosis develops very slowly and is not obvious by looking at the
animal. However, lesions can be detected when the animal is sent for
slaughter. The disease is most often observed in the lungs and/or lymph nodes.
TB can be transmitted from livestock to humans and other animals. No other
TB organism has as great a host range as bovine TB, which can infect all
warm-blooded vertebrates. The causative agent of TB in animal is
_Mycobacterium bovis_. It can be transmitted by close contact such as
nose-to-nose contact or through nasal/oral secretions. - Mod.TG]
